The volume collects nine contribution presenting different ways in **interpreting dreams** in Ancient Near East (Mesopotamia, Syria, Palestine, and Anatolia) and the Bible (with a focus on Joseph’s narrative), including Aramaic texts from Qumran and later Rabbinic literature.

[The book exemplifies the different approaches in the interpretation of dreams in many ancient cultures (Hebrew, Babylonian, Assyrian, and Hittite) underlining political and social issues connected to dream divination.]

